The following are allowed during onsite classes:
- Delivery of lecture and discussion;
- Assessment/quiz;
- Oral defense;
- Performance assessments.

For subjects under the flex blended learning model, face-to-face classes shall be scheduled at least once for the midterm and once for the final period by the subject teacher concerned under the following conditions:
- The schedule is agreed upon by both teacher and students;
- There should be no conflict with other face-to-face classes;
- Permission of the Department Chair should be sought;
- The OUR (Checkers) should be duly informed of the arrangement.

In case of non-compliance with any of the foregoing provisions:
1. First and second instances (on the same or another provision): REMINDER by their respective Chair;
2. Third and fourth instances (on the same and/or another provision): SOFT REPRIMAND by their respective Chair and retraining on the area/s of violation;
3. Fifth and subsequent offenses (on the same provision and/or another provision): MEMO requiring the faculty concerned to explain his side and retraining on the area/s of violation.

Modules to be developed shall have the following parts:
- Gospel/reflection/prayer;
- Learning outcomes;
- Lesson proper and Learning Activities;
- Enabling and Summative Assessments.

The syllabus shall have a uniform format, which includes the following important parts:
- Logo of the University on the left and the logo of the college on the right as part of the heading;
- Course Code;
- Course Title and Course Type;
- Course Credit;
- Blended Learning Modality;
- Prerequisites and Co-requisites;
- Course Description;
- Vision-Mission of DLSUD;
- Institutional Learning Outcomes (ILOs);
- Course Learning Outcomes (at least FIVE Higher Order Thinking Skills);
- Learning Plan, which includes Learning Outcomes, Schedule, Teaching-Learning Activities / Assessment Strategies, Technology Enabler, Online Activities (Synchronous, Asynchronous, and Summative Assessments), Accumulated Hours, face-to-face meetings, and Equivalent Offline Activities.

The following shall be indicated in the syllabus:
- The weekly lessons and tasks of the students;
- The schedules of onsite, synchronous, and asynchronous sessions;
- The institutional self-care week.
